            <dt>How do I make a template?</dt>
            <dd>Drag a 1:1 pixel image onto the canvas and configure in settings, or set an image URL in the template settings. If you need a tool to make pixel art templates, we recommend Paint.NET, GIMP, or a website like <a href="https://www.piskelapp.com/p/create" target="_blank">Piskel</a>. Sure, MS Paint works too.</dd>
            <dt>How do I move a template?</dt>
            <dd>Hold <kbd>CTRL</kbd> (or <kbd>OPTION</kbd> on macOS) and click + drag to move it around. On mobile, you can tap and hold where you want to move the template and click "Move Template Here" in the pop-up. This interface should be better - sorry!</dd>
            <dt>How do I see who placed a pixel?</dt>
            <dd>By shift-clicking (or tap and hold on mobile) a pixel, you can see who placed a pixel, how many pixels they have placed, and when they placed it.</dd>
            <dt>How do I report someone?</dt>
            <dd>Shift-click (or tap and hold on mobile) on a pixel and click the Report button.</dd>
